  "goal": "Redesign retry granularity and rig-status rollup: engine-level retry replaces whole-rig retry. A failed engine is retryable in place without spawning a new rig (which collides with its own upstream artifacts like the PlanDoc). Rig status becomes a rollup over engine states — any engine in failed → rig failed; any engine in retrying → rig running-with-retry. Eliminates the death-spiral where a rate-limited engine stucks the rig, whole-rig retry recreates the rig from scratch, and the recreated rig immediately fails at plan-init because the original's PlanDoc already exists.",
